'''Afghan Film''' also known as '''Afghan Film Organization''' (AFO) is [[Afghanistan]]'s state-run film company. It was established in 1968 and the current president is [[Latif Ahmadi]].<ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm5358615/</ref>

It is also a [[film archive]]. Many of its contents were destroyed by the [[Taliban]], although some staff members saved valuable films risking their own lives.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/film/2008/feb/20/features.afghanistan 'If I find one reel, I must kill you']</ref><ref>[http://www.archivists.org/recognition/sanfrancisco2008-awards.asp#spotlight Awards Acknowledge Outstanding Achievements—2008 SAA Award Recipients]</ref> A number of rescue and archival efforts were chronicled in the 2015 documentary ''[[A Flickering Truth]]''.<ref>[http://www.nzfilm.co.nz/film/a-flickering-truth New Zealand Film Commission - A Flickering Truth]</ref>

