{{Infobox album | name = It's Bad For Ya | type = Live album | artist = [[George Carlin]] | cover = It's Bad for Ya (George Carlin album - cover art).jpg | alt = | released = July 29, 2008 <ref>[https://www.amazon.com/dp/B001BP4U90 "It's Bad For Ya" Release Date at Amazon]</ref> | recorded = March 1, 2008, Wells Fargo Center for the Arts, Santa Rosa, California | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Comedy]] | length = 67:00 | label = [[Eardrum Records|Eardrum]]/[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]] | producer = George Carlin | prev_title = [[Life Is Worth Losing]] | prev_year = 2006 | next_title = [[I Kinda Like It When a Lotta People Die]] | next_year = 2016 }} {{Wikiquote|George Carlin}} '''''It's Bad for Ya''''' is the 19th album, and 14th and final [[HBO]] [[stand-up comedy]] special by stand-up comedian [[George Carlin]]. It was televised live on March 1, 2008, on HBO, less than four months before Carlin died of [[heart failure]] at age 71.<ref>[http://www.hbo.com/events/george-carlin/index.html ''HBO: George Carlin: IT'S BAD FOR YA'']</ref>
The album is the follow-up to the 2005 HBO special ''[[Life Is Worth Losing]]''. Carlin worked on this material since ending his ''Life Is Worth Losing'' tour. The working title for this show was ''The Parade of Useless Bullshit''.
Filmed in the [[Luther Burbank Center for the Arts|Wells Fargo Center for the Arts]] in [[Santa Rosa, California]], the show's stage behind Carlin was designed to represent a cozy living room theme. The CD was released July 29, 2008, and the DVD and Blu-ray Disc on November 25, 2008.
''It's Bad for Ya'' received the [[Grammy Award for Best Comedy Album]], awarded posthumously.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/entertainmentNews/idUSTRE5171UA20090208 |title=Comedian George Carlin wins posthumous Grammy |date=February 8, 2009 |publisher=Reuters}}</ref>
